FBIS4-60677 "drnes103_l_94016" FBIS-NES-94-103 Daily Report 27 May 1994 ISRAEL Sharon Announces Plan To Run for Prime Minister Sharon Announces Plan To Run for Prime Minister TA2705045194 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 0400 GMT 27 May 94 TA2705045194 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el English BFN [Text] Likud Knesset Member Ari'el Sharon says he has decided to bid for the premiership in the next elections. He says he is working to set up a national coalition which will include a number of personalities and groups. He mentioned in particular the Likud's former foreign minister, David Levi. In an interview with Qol Yisra'el, Sharon also said that he was not leaving the Likud party as part of his bid for a leadership role. He hoped there would be primaries to head the national coalition.
